<br>
Swords have fewer high damage styles and all are conditional upon a previous event.  Hammers have the most styles and one is any use.  here  are the numbers<br>
<br>
Weapon     hi dmg     med dmg     Lo/none<br>
                (pre req)<br>
swords      3 (3)          10                2<br>
<br>
Axes         4 (4)            9                2<br>
<br>
Hammers  5 (4)            8                2<br>
<br>
<br>
By level spec. (#) is re req style and * is positional<br>
<br>
Sword<br>
   hi           15(8*), 25(10), 39*<br>
   med       2, 4*, 8*, 10, 18(10), 21*, 29(21*), 34, <br>
                44[29(21)], 50*<br>
   lo/none   6, 12<br>
<br>
Axe<br>
   hi           15*, 25(10), 44(15*), 50(29*)<br>
   med       2, 4*, 8(4), 10, 18(10), 21*, 29*, 34(21*), <br>
                39*<br>
   lo/none   6, 12<br>
<br>
Hammer<br>
   hi           10, 12*, 25(10), 44(29*), 50[34(21*)]<br>
   med       2, 4*, 8(4), 18(10), 21*, 29*, 34(21*), <br>
                39*<br>
   lo/none   6, 15<br>
<br>
The hammer styles have have a main style (ruiner) which is the any time hi damage style, and it is a chain for another hi damage style.  Sword has conditional requirements for eahc style and the chains.<br>
<br>
Axe has a mix of pre reqs or previous styles.  <br>
<br>
My observations are that there is no reason to spec swords at anytime.  They just are too gimped to be useful.  The damage done by a hammer is almost 3 times that of a sword.  This should be corrected in the future or Mythc should just remove the sword as a weapon of choice.<br>
<br>
(I like swords, but even I will be respeccing when possible)<br>
<br>
